    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1953-02-27T16:28:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1953-02-27T16:28:00-05:00" n="409"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d409">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">
                    <persName corresp="#p_MHF1">Matthews</persName> files, lot 53 D 413:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Joint Chiefs of Staff</gloss> to the
                        Commander in Chief Far East (<persName corresp="#p_CGMW1" type="to"
                            >Clark</persName>)</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret<lb/>priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1953-02-27T16:28:00-05:00"
                            >February 27, 1953—4:28 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_JCS1">JCS</gloss> 932476. From <gloss target="#t_JCS1"
                        >JCS</gloss> reur CX 61323.<note n="1" xml:id="d409fn1">Dated Feb. 24, <ref
                            target="#pg_793">p. 793</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>Authy granted you in <gloss target="#t_JCS1">JCS</gloss> 931969<note n="2"
                            xml:id="d409fn2">Dated Feb. 20, <ref target="#pg_790">p.
                            790</ref>;</note> extended to include authy bring to trial <gloss
                            target="#t_POWs1">POWs</gloss> charged with acts of violence against
                        other <gloss target="#t_POWs1">POWs</gloss>, taking place subsequent to
                            <gloss target="#t_POWs1">POW</gloss> segregation and relocation. You
                        also authorized try <gloss target="#t_POWs1">POWs</gloss> who foment or
                        participate in riots or demonstrations which take place subsequent to
                        receipt this msg. Authy re cases involving past riots or demonstrations
                        continues to be withheld.</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>No objection ur proposal confer with ofcrs re nominations to comsn. State
                        advised govts concerned in order assist obtaining full cooperation.</item>
                    <label>3.</label>
                    <item>In view of extension authy granted herein careful consideration shld be
                        given to order in which cases are brought trial. In order create more
                        favorable polit atmosphere it has been suggested trials rotate among cases
                        involving acts against <gloss target="#t_UNC1">UNC</gloss> psnl, acts
                        committed by Commies and acts committed by anti-Commies against fellow
                            <gloss target="#t_POWs1">POWs</gloss>. However, order of trials left to
                        ur discretion.</item>
                </list>
            </div>
        </body>
